+## Summary
+Total: 5 findings (0 P0, 2 P1, 3 P2, 0 P3)
 
-Findings:
-
-1. P1 - `x.jsx:2955`, `x.jsx:3144-3163`, `CartView.jsx:302-307`, `CartView.jsx:463`
-Why it matters: guest name persistence is still broken before the first hall order. The edited name is only written to `localStorage` (`menuapp_guest_name`) and never becomes the fallback display name in the drawer. On submit, a new guest is created with `addGuestToSession(session.id, null, deviceId)`, so the persisted name is not attached to the created guest record either. After refresh / browser kill, the user falls back to `Guest` again.
-Concrete fix: keep a separate persisted guest-name value and use it whenever `currentGuest?.name` is empty. When creating a guest, pass that persisted name into `addGuestToSession(...)` if supported, otherwise update the newly created guest immediately after creation and sync `currentGuest` / `sessionGuests`.
-
-2. P1 - `x.jsx:169-185`, `x.jsx:1456-1473`, `x.jsx:2395-2407`
-Why it matters: cart restore is keyed only by `partnerId` (`menuapp_cart_${partnerId}`). After a browser kill, reopening the same restaurant in another mode or on another table restores the old draft into the new context. Initial restore also skips the mode-availability filter that only runs inside `handleModeChange()`, so stale items can survive into a different flow.
-Concrete fix: scope cart storage by partner + mode + table context, for example `menuapp_cart_${partnerId}_${orderMode}_${currentTableId || 'no_table'}`. During restore, run the same availability filtering used in `handleModeChange()` before `setCart(savedCart)`.
+## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
+- Overall clarity: 5
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): none
